	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64854753"><p>Well, "irreversable" is in the title here, but in the text the consequences are that an overshoot could "cause sea level rises and other disastrous repercussions that might last millennia."  The <a href="https://www.nature.com/articles/s41586-024-08020-9" title="nature.com">actual article</a> [nature.com] doesn't use the word "irreversable".
</p><p>So, effects are not forever, just thousands of years.
</p><p>(A possible better news story is this one: <a href="https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/256978/reversing-global-warming-part-climate-overshoot/" title="imperial.ac.uk">https://www.imperial.ac.uk/new...</a> [imperial.ac.uk] . Here the phrasing is "Temporarily exceeding global temperature rise of 1.5C likely to come with long-term consequences."</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64854753">
<span class="ind"></span><a id="reply_link_64854753" class="btn link" href="//news.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23483291&amp;op=Reply&amp;threshold=1&amp;commentsort=0&amp;mode=thread&amp;pid=64854753" onclick="D2.replyTo(64854753); return false;">Reply to This</a> <span class="ind"></span><a class="btn link" rel="nofollow" href="//news.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23483291&amp;threshold=1&amp;commentsort=0&amp;mode=thread&amp;cid=64854701" onclick="return D2.selectParent(64854701)">Parent</a> 	<a rel="nofollow" href="#" class="comment_share_toggle btn link">Share</a>
